14 Apr 2016In line with the 2016 State of the Nation Address (SONA) pronouncements and government priorities, the Deputy Minister of Communications, Ms. Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams (MP) will lead a post SoNA Information Seminar in the Mbhashe Local Municipality, Idutywa. Post SoNA Information Seminar affords Government the opportunity to engage and reflect on service delivery, plans, milestones and challenges to date as part of ongoing feedback to communities. Preceding the post SoNA information seminar will be a project monitoring visit wherein the Deputy Minister will check on the progress of the Online Video Editing course which is currently ongoing at the King Sabata Dalindyebo (KSD) TVET College in Cicira, Mthatha.In her 2015 Budget Vote Speech, the Deputy Minister committed to, train unemployed youth, learners and teachers on Online Video Editing Software. This project has been rolled out in partnership with MICT SETA and Atos, benefiting 70 unemployed youth in Eastern Cape, 40 in the Western Cape and 40 in Gauteng.The media are hereby cordially invited to the event and the details are as follows:Part 1: Online Video Editing monitoring visit Date: 18 April 2016 Venue: KSD TVET College, Cicira Time: 09h00 10h30Part 2: Post SoNA Information Seminar Session Date: 18 April 2016 Venue: King Hintsa TVET College Time: 12h30 15h30Opportunity will be given to journalists for interviews and photo opportunities.For media RSVP: please contact: Tabita Ngqunge from GCIS at: 072 344 7712/ tabita@gcis.gov.za) or Ndyebo Kopo from GCIS at 083 464 9529/ ndyebok@gcis.gov.za Enquiries: Ndlelantle Pinyana 076 142 8606 or Nthabeleng Mokitimi: 073 222 5522Issued by Government Communications (GCIS) on behalf of Ministry of Communications